Spaghetti with Spring Vegetables
  - Cook's Country

6 oz cherry tomatoes, halved
6 tbsp evoo + extra for drizzling
1 small garlic clove, minced + 4 cloves sliced thin
salt and pepper
1 lb spaghetti
1 zucchini, halved lengthwise and sliced 1/4" thick
1/8 tsp red pepper flakes
1 lb asparagus, trimmed, and cut on bias into 1" lengths
1 c frozen peas, thawed
1/4 c minced fresh chives
1 tbsp lemon juice
1/4 c grated pecorino romano + extra for serving
2 tbsp torn fresh mint leaves

Toss tomatoes, 1 tbsp oil, minced garlic, 1/4 tsp salt, and 1/4 tsp pepper together in a bowl, set aside. Bring 4 qts water to boil in large dutch oven. Add pasta and 1 tbsp salt and cook, stirring often, until al dente. Drain pasta and return to pot. Meanwhile, heat 3 tbsp oil in 12" skillet over medium low heat until shimmering. Add zucchini, pepper flakes, sliced garlic, and 1/2 tsp salt and cook, covered, until zucchini softenes and breaks down, 10-15 min, stirring occasionally. Add asparagus, peas, and 3/4 c water and bring to simmer over medium high heat. cover and cook until asparagus is crsp tender, ~2 min. Add vegetable mixture, chives, lemon juice, and remaining 2 tbsp oil to pasta and toss to combine. Transfer to serving bowl, sprinkle with pecorino, and drizzle with extra oil. Spoon tomatoes and their juices over top and sprinkle with mint. Serve, passing extra pecornio separately.
